-- в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ

вҠў format-spec
  given collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirements вүЎ [26 concrete requirements]
  given requestвҶ’text вүЎ "Build me a chat app"
  yield specification

  вҲҙ Format В«collect-requirementsвҶ’all-requirementsВ» as a structured requirements
    specification document for the original request В«requestвҶ’textВ».
    Group requirements by category (functional, non-functional, security,
    UX). Number each requirement. Mark which were explicit vs implicit.

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The LLM groups the 26 requirements into categories, numbers them,
-- and marks provenance (explicit vs implicit).

  yield specification вүЎ "REQUIREMENTS SPECIFICATION вҖ” 'Build me a chat app'

FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS:
  F1. [explicit] The system must support sending and receiving text messages between two or more parties
  F2. [explicit] The deliverable is a software application with a user interface
  F3. [explicit] The application must be built from scratch
  F4. [explicit] The application is for the requester's use or ownership
  F5. [implicit] Users must be able to create accounts or authenticate to identify themselves
  F6. [implicit] The app must support at least 1-on-1 conversations
  F7. [implicit] All messages stored for minimum 365 days
  F8. [implicit] Message retrieval in under 2 seconds within retention period
  F9. [implicit] Conversation history paginated at 50 messages per page
  F10. [implicit] Queue outgoing messages locally when offline
  F11. [implicit] Sync missed messages within 5 seconds of reconnection
  F12. [implicit] Queued messages sent in FIFO order
  F13. [implicit] Retain queued messages for up to 24 hours offline

NON-FUNCTIONAL / PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS:
  N1. [implicit] Delivery latency p50 < 200ms on broadband
  N2. [implicit] Delivery latency p99 < 1000ms on broadband
  N3. [implicit] Delivery latency p50 < 500ms on mobile 4G
  N4. [implicit] Sustain latency targets under 10,000 concurrent users
  N5. [implicit] Messages survive server restarts (durability guarantee)

SECURITY REQUIREMENTS:
  S1. [implicit] Only conversation participants can read messages (access control)
  S2. [implicit] Messages encrypted in transit via TLS 1.2+
  S3. [implicit] Messages encrypted at rest via AES-256

UX REQUIREMENTS:
  U1. [implicit] In-app notifications within 1 second of message delivery
  U2. [implicit] Push notifications within 5 seconds of delivery
  U3. [implicit] Users can disable push notifications per conversation
  U4. [implicit] Notification preview shows first 100 characters
  U5. [implicit] Offline indicator within 3 seconds of connectivity loss

NOTES:
  - 4 explicit requirements extracted directly from request text
  - 22 implicit requirements derived from domain conventions
  - 1 requirement deferred: admin access consent mechanism (needs design decision)
  - Completeness score: 9.6/10"

-- oracle checks:
--   вҠЁ specification groups requirements by category вҶ’ вң“
--     4 categories: Functional, Non-Functional, Security, UX
--   вҠЁ specification numbers each requirement вҶ’ вң“
--     F1-F13, N1-N5, S1-S3, U1-U5 (26 total)
--   вҠЁ specification marks each requirement as explicit or implicit вҶ’ вң“
--     [explicit] and [implicit] tags on every requirement
--   вҠЁ every requirement from all-requirements appears in the specification вҶ’ вң“
--     All 26 concrete requirements mapped to a numbered entry

